===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A hardened rectangular block of [[mud]], [[clay]] etc., used for [[build]]ing.
#: ''This wall is made of '''bricks'''''.
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} Considered collectively, as a building material.
#: ''This house is made of '''brick'''''.
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} Something shaped like a brick.
#: ''a plastic explosive '''brick'''''
# {{context|dated|lang=en}} A [[helpful]] and [[reliable]] person.
#: ''Thanks for helping me wash the car. You're a '''brick'''.''
#* {{quote-book|year=1863|author=Elizabeth Caroline Grey|title=Good Society; Or, Contrasts of Character|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=JB6BWYCaQS8C&pg=PA72&dq=%22you%27re+a+brick%22&as_brr=3|page=72|passage=“It's easy to see you're a '''brick'''!” replied Lady Augusta, and the laugh again became general.}}
#* {{quote-book|year=1906|author={{w|Edith Nesbit}}|title=[[w:The Railway Children|The Railway Children]]|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=tLVPkFHLEZMC&pg=PA168&dq=%22you%27re+a+brick%22&as_brr=3&sig=bMkcYZ4ym_R-anlb_W206onJOf4|page=168|passage=‘Somebody had to stay with you,’ said Bobbie.<br>‘Tell you what, Bobbie,’ said Jim, ‘you’re a '''brick'''. Shake.’}}
#* {{quote-book|year=1960|author=W.W. Jacobs|title=Cargoes|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=o2tFTib3eGQC&pg=PA45&dq=%22you%27re+a+brick%22+date:1940-1990&lr=&as_brr=3&sig=GQAlsIu4mx0WPYYdARw7Wxnbg9k|isbn=0828314306|page=45|passage=“Well, I’ll do what I can for you,” said the seaman, …“If you were only shorter, I'd lend you some clothes.”<br>“You're a '''brick''',” said the soldier gratefully.}}
# {{context|basketball|slang|lang=en}} A [[shot]] which misses, particularly one which bounces directly out of the basket because of a too-flat trajectory, as if the ball were a heavier object.
#: ''We can't win if we keep throwing up '''bricks''' from three-point land.''
# {{context|informal|lang=en}} A [[power brick]]; an external [[power supply]] consisting of a small [[box]] with an integral [[male]] [[power plug]] and an attached [[electric cord]] terminating in another power plug.
# {{context|technology|slang|lang=en}} An electronic device, especially a heavy box-shaped one, that has become non-functional or obsolete.
# {{context|firearms|lang=en}} a carton of 500 rimfire cartridges, which forms the approximate size and shape of a brick.
# {{context|poker slang|lang=en}} A [[community card]] (usually the [[turn]] or the [[river]]) which does not improve a player's hand.
#: {{usex|The two of clubs was a complete '''brick''' on the river|lang=en}}

